1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,917
Chefs who have left the show
are coming back one after another.

2
00:00:17,984 --> 00:00:19,819
Following Chef Kang-rok last week,

3
00:00:19,886 --> 00:00:23,456
we have Chef Edward back here with us!

4
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:25,759
WELCOME BACK

5
00:00:28,762 --> 00:00:30,697
-I'm good.
-You're good.

6
00:00:30,764 --> 00:00:33,933
-Anyway, your new hair looks amazing.
-Thank you.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,402
-Reminds me of Sechs Kies.
-Actually,

8
00:00:35,468 --> 00:00:37,737
I got my hair done because of Hyun-suk.

9
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:38,972
-Because of Hyun-suk?
-Why?

10
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,673
We're the same age,

11
00:00:40,740 --> 00:00:44,811
but too many people say
that I look much older than him.

12
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,179
That sounds like a problem.

13
00:00:46,246 --> 00:00:49,182
But that's not your fault, Kyun.

14
00:00:49,249 --> 00:00:51,584
It's just that I look too young…

15
00:00:51,651 --> 00:00:52,652
I'm sorry.

16
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:55,789
-You said you'd stop your yapping.
-I know. I'm sorry.

17
00:00:55,855 --> 00:00:58,558
Anyway, we're so happy to have you back.

18
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:00,660
It looks like
everyone is happy to see him,

19
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:04,464
-but Sung-jun has his head hung low.
-Sung-jun?

20
00:01:04,531 --> 00:01:05,632
This is another emergency.

21
00:01:05,698 --> 00:01:07,200
-Is it?
-Why is that?

22
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:10,904
I was already busy
holding <i>CCW2</i> chefs in check,

23
00:01:10,970 --> 00:01:11,938
but my sworn enemy,

24
00:01:12,005 --> 00:01:14,207
-Chef Edward, has returned.
-That's right.

25
00:01:14,274 --> 00:01:17,110
He also got his hair done
to take all the buzz.

26
00:01:17,177 --> 00:01:19,279
-This guy and his buzz.
-I should dye my hair too.

27
00:01:19,345 --> 00:01:20,747
You know what?

28
00:01:20,814 --> 00:01:24,317
-I think I have the most buzzworthy news.
-What is it now?

29
00:01:24,384 --> 00:01:26,286
-I was surprised too.
-The president of France,

30
00:01:26,352 --> 00:01:29,322
-President Macron plans to visit Korea.
-Yes, I heard that.

31
00:01:29,389 --> 00:01:30,957
And he'll have a state banquet

32
00:01:31,024 --> 00:01:33,093
-with President Lee.
-Wait.

33
00:01:33,159 --> 00:01:36,029
Chef Son Jong-won of our show…

34
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:38,264
"BRAVO, CHEF!" COMPLIMENTS FROM MACRON
PRESIDENT LEE, "FULL OF CULTURAL RESPECT"

35
00:01:38,331 --> 00:01:40,033
He's on another level!

36
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,267
I'm jealous.

37
00:01:41,334 --> 00:01:44,370
-I'll be cooking just for four.
-Really?

38
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,239
-It's a private dinner.
-That's so cool.

39
00:01:46,306 --> 00:01:48,441
If you're looking to make pizza…

40
00:01:48,741 --> 00:01:50,376
DOESN'T MISS A CHANCE TO BUTT IN

41
00:01:50,443 --> 00:01:52,412
-I can make the pizza.
-Never.

42
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:56,149
He's the only chef who has
two restaurants with one Michelin star,

43
00:01:56,216 --> 00:01:57,584
in both French and Korean cuisine.

44
00:01:57,650 --> 00:01:58,918
-That's right.
-Double stars.

45
00:01:58,985 --> 00:02:01,054
The Korean and French presidents
would be dining together,

46
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,689
so they must've thought of him.

47
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:05,358
-That's right.
-I knew it'd be him.

48
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:07,293
Because when he was our guest,
he ate his dish

49
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,728
and gave him double hearts.

50
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:09,662
He's giving you his love.

51
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:12,398
WAS EVEN APPOINTED
AS THE EXPORT POWERHOUSE

52
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:15,602
-The Korean cuisine export powerhouse.
-Yes, that was on the episode.

53
00:02:15,668 --> 00:02:18,271
This is the level
that <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> is at now.

54
00:02:18,338 --> 00:02:20,740
We may even get to
invite national leaders here.

55
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:22,709
We can have the World Summit on our show.

56
00:02:22,775 --> 00:02:24,043
Let's do it here.

57
00:02:24,377 --> 00:02:26,446
WELL-SUITED AS A PLACE OF HARMONY?

58
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:30,083
Anyway, please let the Blue House know
how we're doing.

59
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,252
First, I'll do a great job at dinner,

60
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:34,787
and if possible,
I'll even ask President Macron

61
00:02:34,854 --> 00:02:36,890
if he can join us next Chuseok.

62
00:02:36,956 --> 00:02:38,892
-He'll cast him.
-He'll go and cast him.

63
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:40,160
You'll cast him? Goodness.

64
00:02:40,627 --> 00:02:44,464
THE BANQUET ENDED SUCCESSFULLY

65
00:02:45,965 --> 00:02:48,001
It's now time to welcome
the fridge owners.

66
00:02:48,067 --> 00:02:50,670
They've also been quite buzzworthy lately.

67
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:53,540
Do you see
that rigid expression on Chef Sung-jun?

68
00:02:53,606 --> 00:02:57,810
I'm sure the guests will
put a big smile on his face.

69
00:02:57,877 --> 00:02:59,746
-Are they K-pop stars?
-They'll do that.

70
00:02:59,812 --> 00:03:02,649
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

71
00:03:02,715 --> 00:03:03,883
Come on out!

72
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:06,085
They're finally here.

73
00:03:06,152 --> 00:03:07,854
Today's fridge owners!

74
00:03:07,921 --> 00:03:12,225
Right now, it's Girls' Generation!
Please welcome Tiffany and Hyo-yeon!

75
00:03:12,292 --> 00:03:13,993
-Welcome.
-My world while I was in the army.

76
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:15,662
THE REAL FAN MAKES A BIG FUSS

77
00:03:15,728 --> 00:03:16,996
One, two, three.

78
00:03:17,063 --> 00:03:19,432
-Hello, we're Girls' Generation.
-Hello, we're Girls' Generation.

79
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:22,602
THE BONA FIDE LEGENDARY IDOL GROUP

80
00:03:22,902 --> 00:03:25,838
NOW CREATING BUZZ WITH THEIR SOLO CAREERS

81
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:27,874
TIFFANY & HYO-YEON

82
00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:30,076
We're here with two charmers.

83
00:03:30,143 --> 00:03:31,311
This is great.

84
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,646
-I feel a bit shy to sit here.
-Why?

85
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:35,381
I'm really

86
00:03:35,448 --> 00:03:36,282
nervous.

87
00:03:36,349 --> 00:03:38,151
-No, don't be.
-Come on.

88
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:40,753
You can't be nervous. It's been ages
since you started your career.

89
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:43,790
-I'm on my favorite program.
-Actually,

90
00:03:43,856 --> 00:03:46,192
-they're huge fans of the show.
-We are.

91
00:03:46,259 --> 00:03:47,093
IT'S TRUE

92
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,561
Do you watch our show often?

93
00:03:48,628 --> 00:03:52,098
I watched every single episode
since the show has begun.

94
00:03:52,165 --> 00:03:53,499
I even watched <i>Cook Representative</i>.

95
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,001
-You know that show?
-Of course.

96
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:57,170
I watch everything, even reruns.

97
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:59,539
I have a few favorite episodes

98
00:03:59,606 --> 00:04:02,041
that I've downloaded
so I can watch them on flights.

99
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:03,643
I rewatch the episodes again and again.

100
00:04:03,943 --> 00:04:04,944
APPROVED AS A FAN

101
00:04:05,011 --> 00:04:06,980
-A true fan.
-Anything off the top of your head?

102
00:04:07,046 --> 00:04:08,648
The most shocking episode

103
00:04:08,715 --> 00:04:10,783
was Chef Kim Poong's dung.

104
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:13,019
Don't say "dung"!

105
00:04:13,386 --> 00:04:15,021
TOO MUCH HAS BEEN OMITTED

106
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:17,090
"Dung"? What are you talking about?

107
00:04:17,156 --> 00:04:18,491
Not dung loach, just "dung."

108
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:21,661
-It's always saved on my device.
-Was it that shocking?

109
00:04:21,728 --> 00:04:25,331
Hyo-yeon has something
she'd like to say on the show.

110
00:04:25,398 --> 00:04:27,433
I recently released my new song.

111
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,168
<i>It's called "MOVEURBODY."</i>

112
00:04:29,235 --> 00:04:30,770
RECENTLY RELEASED "MOVEURBODY"

113
00:04:31,537 --> 00:04:32,372
<i>"MOVEURBODY."</i>

114
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:36,109
It's a good song to listen to
when you want to feel a storm of energy.

115
00:04:36,175 --> 00:04:37,343
I want to dance.

116
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:38,611
THE DANCERS REACT IMMEDIATELY

117
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:40,313
We can't move on
without mentioning Sung-jun

118
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,048
when members
of Girls' Generation are here.

119
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,650
He was quite depressed

120
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:45,551
to see Chef Edward with us today,

121
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,553
but he looks happy now.

122
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:48,721
-I feel great.
-I see.

123
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,523
-Is it my birthday?
-His connection to Girls' Generation.

124
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:56,829
I had visited his restaurant once before.

125
00:04:56,896 --> 00:04:59,032
When I was almost done with my meal,

126
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:03,903
he came and quietly said,
"I was a member of HwaSuEunWa."

127
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:05,705
-He did?
-And when people say that,

128
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:10,143
I can always kind of tell
if they're my fan or another member's.

129
00:05:10,209 --> 00:05:13,279
So I was thinking,
"He probably isn't my fan."

130
00:05:13,346 --> 00:05:15,915
Before I left, he said,
"I'm Sooyoung's fan."

131
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:17,016
Didn't ask, don't care.

132
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,384
"Didn't ask, don't care?"

133
00:05:18,451 --> 00:05:21,587
-Didn't ask, don't care!
-Why did you tell her that?

134
00:05:21,654 --> 00:05:24,057
-You should've stopped at HwaSuEunWa!
-Yes!

135
00:05:24,123 --> 00:05:25,124
He should be punched.

136
00:05:25,191 --> 00:05:26,426
Is Sooyoung aware of this?

137
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:28,494
-She is.
-She is?

138
00:05:28,561 --> 00:05:32,532
She once tagged me on her Instagram story
and uploaded a screenshot.

139
00:05:34,033 --> 00:05:37,036
Why don't you leave
a video message for Sooyoung?

140
00:05:37,103 --> 00:05:38,171
Hello.

141
00:05:38,237 --> 00:05:41,708
I'm Kwon Sung-jun, and I was active
on the website as "Sooyoung's Hubby."

142
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:43,443
-Please visit my restaurant…
-What's with him?

143
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:46,612
…and I'll prepare a delicious meal
like the professional chef that I am.

144
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:48,614
-I'll be waiting.
-He's so serious.

145
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:50,416
-He's dead serious.
-He is.

146
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:51,818
I don't like the look of his philtrum.

147
00:05:51,884 --> 00:05:54,987
Don't you hate that face?
Why do I hate that expression so much?

148
00:05:55,054 --> 00:05:57,690
Tiffany isn't just a singer anymore.

149
00:05:57,757 --> 00:06:01,928
She has widened her career
into acting and musical acting.

150
00:06:01,994 --> 00:06:04,630
This is my tenth anniversary
as a solo artist,

151
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:08,935
so I'm planning to release
my first full album on May 11th.

152
00:06:09,001 --> 00:06:11,771
And my upcoming musical
is called <i>Yumi's Cells,</i>

153
00:06:11,838 --> 00:06:15,308
where I'll be playing Yumi
in the musical adaptation

154
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,378
of the beloved webtoon series and drama.

155
00:06:18,444 --> 00:06:21,280
Please show lots of love for <i>Yumi's Cells</i>.

156
00:06:21,347 --> 00:06:23,082
-You're busy.
-She really is.

157
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:24,150
HER YEAR IS ALREADY FULL

158
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:26,185
In the midst of her busy schedule…

159
00:06:26,252 --> 00:06:28,254
-There's great news.
-Yes.

160
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:30,757
She recently registered her marriage

161
00:06:30,823 --> 00:06:33,226
with actor Byun Yo-han.

162
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:34,660
CONGRATULATIONS

163
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:38,331
-Congratulations to the beautiful couple.
-Thank you.

164
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,565
I'm jealous.

165
00:06:39,632 --> 00:06:40,767
Tiffany is now a newlywed.

166
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,668
-A newlywed.
-A newlywed.

167
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,103
-A married woman.
-A married woman.

168
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:46,005
-That feels weird.
-Yes?

169
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,440
"Off the market."

170
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:48,775
Off the market.

171
00:06:48,841 --> 00:06:49,842
-Yes.
-Off the market.

172
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,210
-What's the difference?
-What is it?

173
00:06:51,277 --> 00:06:54,881
If I were to consider
the future of Girls' Generation…

174
00:06:55,448 --> 00:06:58,317
-Off the market.
-Nuance is everything.

175
00:06:58,384 --> 00:06:59,519
We've been discontinued.

176
00:06:59,786 --> 00:07:01,220
OFF THE MARKET
AND THE DISCONTINUED MEN

177
00:07:01,287 --> 00:07:03,189
This side has been discontinued.

178
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,391
-Please say that I'm sold out.
-That's cool.

179
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:06,993
That's nice too.

180
00:07:07,059 --> 00:07:09,796
-Salt, out.
-"Salt, out"?

181
00:07:09,862 --> 00:07:11,731
We can't call her married.

182
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:14,333
-We'll say she's off the market.
-Off the market.

183
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:17,670
I'm sure the members
were surprised to hear the news.

184
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:21,007
I was especially surprised
because it was her.

185
00:07:21,073 --> 00:07:24,243
I always thought, "It'd be a miracle
if she even got married."

186
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:28,548
-Why?
-"It'd be a miracle if she got married"?

187
00:07:28,614 --> 00:07:31,017
Because she's all about her work.

188
00:07:32,418 --> 00:07:36,522
I always thought she wouldn't
fall out of love with her work.

189
00:07:36,589 --> 00:07:40,359
That was why it was a surprise for me.

190
00:07:40,426 --> 00:07:42,595
But you decided to seize love over work.

191
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:46,799
It's because I found someone with whom
I wanted to spend my precious time with.

192
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:48,501
That's nice.

193
00:07:48,568 --> 00:07:50,269
Did anyone try to stop you?

194
00:07:50,336 --> 00:07:52,805
-It was our youngest one.
-The youngest? Seohyun?

195
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:54,874
She suddenly began to cry and said,

196
00:07:54,941 --> 00:07:57,610
"Tiffany, I can't let you go."

197
00:07:58,578 --> 00:07:59,946
So I said, "Seohyun."

198
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:03,749
I SHOULD GET MARRIED…

199
00:08:03,816 --> 00:08:06,018
What does "dirty seven" mean?

200
00:08:06,085 --> 00:08:07,520
-She's 37 years old.
-Right.

201
00:08:09,055 --> 00:08:10,756
-What's up?
-He didn't understand.

202
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:11,991
-He quietly asked…
-Be quiet.

203
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:13,693
"What does 'dirty seven' mean?"

204
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,161
DON'T PAY ANY ATTENTION

205
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:18,531
We've all lived
through Girls' Generation's era, right?

206
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:20,066
But he listened to <i>Women's Era</i>.

207
00:08:20,132 --> 00:08:22,335
It was <i>Here's to a Long Life</i> for me.

208
00:08:22,401 --> 00:08:25,071
<i>Here's to a Long Life?</i>
You have to go way back.

209
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:27,139
-What is that?
-Chef Edward.

210
00:08:27,206 --> 00:08:29,742
You did a program with Yo-han, right?

211
00:08:29,809 --> 00:08:31,210
-He did.
-I did.

212
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:34,380
I was very happy
while I worked with Yo-han.

213
00:08:35,481 --> 00:08:36,782
He was so nice,

214
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:38,751
and we became great friends.

215
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:41,854
These days, he seems busy.

216
00:08:41,921 --> 00:08:43,689
So he stopped contacting me.

217
00:08:43,756 --> 00:08:45,658
He hasn't contacted him.

218
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:47,093
He somehow grew on me.

219
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:48,160
AWW

220
00:08:48,227 --> 00:08:49,462
He's disappointed.

221
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:52,565
No, he mentioned you so many times.

222
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:55,735
-He did?
-Yes, he really adores you.

223
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:58,104
-Yes.
-That makes me feel great.

224
00:08:58,170 --> 00:09:00,106
Don't you think they make a great couple?

225
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:03,075
-They're perfect.
-Thank you.

226
00:09:03,142 --> 00:09:06,445
Many people may be wondering

227
00:09:06,512 --> 00:09:09,682
about how you registered your marriage
before you had your wedding.

228
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:11,551
-Yes.
-How did that happen?

229
00:09:11,617 --> 00:09:13,819
The wedding ceremony is important,

230
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:19,191
but it was more important for us
to spend every single day together.

231
00:09:19,258 --> 00:09:22,228
So we decided to be lawfully wedded first.

232
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:23,963
You wanted to be together
as soon as possible!

233
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,431
Yes.

234
00:09:25,498 --> 00:09:28,334
-She wanted to start their life together.
-That's a good decision.

235
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,036
We received a tip.

236
00:09:30,102 --> 00:09:32,071
Among our single chefs,

237
00:09:32,138 --> 00:09:33,839
one of them has a dream

238
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:35,775
of having a wedding
at a raw fish restaurant.

239
00:09:35,841 --> 00:09:37,643
-I think I know who.
-Who is it?

240
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:39,478
-Who is it?
-It's great news for the guests.

241
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:41,480
-It's me.
-It's Nam-no.

242
00:09:41,547 --> 00:09:42,548
-Why?
-Nam-no.

243
00:09:42,615 --> 00:09:43,749
-He's different.
-Actually,

244
00:09:43,816 --> 00:09:47,787
I wanted to serve the guests
delicious food.

245
00:09:47,853 --> 00:09:49,822
-You want to throw a proper feast.
-A nice meal.

246
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:51,924
I'll rent out an entire building
at the Noryangjin Fish Market.

247
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:53,492
WOW

248
00:09:53,559 --> 00:09:55,294
I'm suddenly intrigued.

249
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:56,462
Isn't it a nice idea?

250
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:59,065
Instead of a wedding speech,
I'll have Chef Ho-young come

251
00:09:59,131 --> 00:10:02,535
and do a tuna cutting show
with a 200-kg tuna.

252
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,236
-Tuna cutting.
-A tuna cutting show.

253
00:10:04,303 --> 00:10:06,405
I haven't asked him yet,
but I'm sure he'll do it.

254
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:09,542
-Will you pay travel expenses?
-Travel expenses?

255
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:11,243
IF YES, I'LL BE THERE

256
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:13,045
-You have to pay him.
-After that,

257
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:15,848
we'll go to a butcher shop restaurant
at Majang-dong.

258
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:16,849
With the guests?

259
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,718
-He's only doing feasts.
-Fish then meat.

260
00:10:19,819 --> 00:10:20,820
I can see that.

261
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:22,888
IMAGINING THE FISH RESTAURANT WEDDING

262
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,091
Why don't you do it first?

263
00:10:25,157 --> 00:10:26,959
A raw fish restaurant?

264
00:10:28,561 --> 00:10:30,696
"Tiffany's wedding,
held at a raw fish restaurant."

265
00:10:30,763 --> 00:10:32,531
"Reception at Majang-dong."

266
00:10:33,866 --> 00:10:35,101
I'LL BE THERE

267
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,702
-I have another tip.
-Yes?

268
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:38,938
At Chef Jong-won's wedding…

269
00:10:39,005 --> 00:10:40,106
HUH?

270
00:10:40,172 --> 00:10:43,209
…there's someone who wants
to make his wish come true.

271
00:10:43,275 --> 00:10:44,410
Why at his wedding?

272
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:46,979
-It's not their wedding.
-Why at Jong-won's wedding and not theirs?

273
00:10:47,046 --> 00:10:49,248
Am I getting married? I guess I should.

274
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,617
-It's Chef Hyun-suk.
-What is it?

275
00:10:51,684 --> 00:10:54,820
He wishes to sing the wedding song.

276
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:56,689
OH…

277
00:10:56,756 --> 00:10:59,025
If you want to sing, go to a karaoke room!

278
00:10:59,091 --> 00:11:01,460
Why would you do that at his wedding?

279
00:11:01,527 --> 00:11:04,230
Find a coin karaoke machine.
I'll give you some coins.

280
00:11:04,296 --> 00:11:05,464
HAHAHAHA

281
00:11:06,198 --> 00:11:07,400
It's not that.

282
00:11:07,466 --> 00:11:10,403
We're close, aren't we? And actually,

283
00:11:10,469 --> 00:11:12,838
I've sung quite often at chefs' weddings.

284
00:11:12,905 --> 00:11:14,140
He has.

285
00:11:14,206 --> 00:11:17,443
So since we're close,
I just said I'd do it if he got married.

286
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:20,980
-Maybe that's why he's not marrying.
-That's why.

287
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:22,882
I'm not someone
who's dying to sing at weddings.

288
00:11:22,948 --> 00:11:26,752
I don't go to chefs who'll marry and say,
"Would you like me to sing for you?"

289
00:11:26,819 --> 00:11:28,020
I don't do that!

290
00:11:28,087 --> 00:11:30,256
-Why don't we ask Jong-won?
-Yes.

291
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:31,957
Would you like him to sing?

292
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:33,059
I gave it a thought,

293
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:34,593
but I want it to be solemn.

294
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:36,395
WEDDING SINGER CHOI, BANNED

295
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:39,265
-He wants a solemn wedding.
-So no wedding songs.

296
00:11:39,331 --> 00:11:42,435
-That's my dream. A solemn wedding.
-That's his dream.

297
00:11:42,501 --> 00:11:45,571
Let's go find a coin karaoke after
his wedding. I'll listen to you sing.

298
00:11:45,638 --> 00:11:47,973
He declined your offer respectfully.

299
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,309
Don't you dare get married
without letting me sing.

300
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,378
THE WEDDING SINGER KING'S SALES SECRET

301
00:11:52,445 --> 00:11:53,579
How scary.

302
00:11:53,646 --> 00:11:56,182
-Make sure you invite him!
-At the fish restaurant.

303
00:11:56,248 --> 00:11:57,683
-There is…
-Yes.

304
00:11:57,750 --> 00:12:01,520
…something Chef Eun-yeong
wants to share for the first time.

305
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:02,722
-No way.
-Finally?

306
00:12:02,788 --> 00:12:04,457
-No way. Wait.
-What is it, Eun-yeong?

307
00:12:04,523 --> 00:12:05,991
-What is it?
-I'm about to

308
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:08,694
go off the market.

309
00:12:09,161 --> 00:12:10,129
PARK EUN-YEONG'S WEDDING

310
00:12:10,196 --> 00:12:12,031
Are you announcing your marriage here?

311
00:12:12,264 --> 00:12:13,699
CONGRATULATIONS

312
00:12:13,766 --> 00:12:15,835
-Are you getting married?
-I am.

313
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:18,471
I wondered where I should share it,

314
00:12:18,537 --> 00:12:21,474
and I thought this was the best place
since I think of it like my home.

315
00:12:21,540 --> 00:12:24,243
-That's the right call.
-Do you have a date?

316
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:26,378
-It's in May.
-A bride in May.

317
00:12:26,445 --> 00:12:28,214
-Congratulations.
-Where did you meet him?

318
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,216
-It was a blind date.
-I see.

319
00:12:30,282 --> 00:12:32,118
Did you have time for that
despite your busy work?

320
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:34,587
We met on a blind date a while ago,

321
00:12:34,653 --> 00:12:35,721
but it didn't work out then.

322
00:12:35,788 --> 00:12:37,490
We got together after a while.

323
00:12:37,556 --> 00:12:41,594
Was there anything special
that you saw in him?

324
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:44,363
Most people come to me and ask me
to make something delicious, right?

325
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:45,865
But he was the only one

326
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:49,935
who offered to make something for me
instead of asking me to cook.

327
00:12:50,002 --> 00:12:51,270
Is he a chef?

328
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:53,672
-He isn't.
-He's not even a chef.

329
00:12:53,739 --> 00:12:55,908
-"Take a break while you're with me."
-Yes.

330
00:12:55,975 --> 00:12:57,843
I thought that was endearing.

331
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,145
SUCH A SWEET GESTURE

332
00:12:59,211 --> 00:13:01,714
-That's so cool.
-That was how he captured her heart.

333
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:05,017
I'm sure he has watched our show.

334
00:13:05,084 --> 00:13:07,553
-Yes, he often watches us.
-I see.

335
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:11,056
-Has he seen your eyes when you danced?
-The crazy eyes?

336
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:13,559
-Has he said anything?
-Has he watched your crazy eyes?

337
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:14,860
"The crazy eyes."

338
00:13:14,927 --> 00:13:16,829
He didn't say anything much, but he asked,

339
00:13:16,896 --> 00:13:18,664
"Is your restaurant not doing well?"

340
00:13:18,998 --> 00:13:21,834
WHISPERING
DARLING, DID YOUR SALES DROP?

341
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:23,402
EMBARRASSED

342
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:25,504
He's asking if you're trying that hard

343
00:13:25,571 --> 00:13:28,307
-because your restaurant is in trouble?
-"Do you have to go that far?"

344
00:13:28,374 --> 00:13:30,709
The more aggressively I dance,

345
00:13:30,776 --> 00:13:32,444
the more reservations he makes.

346
00:13:32,511 --> 00:13:35,047
He wants to be the one
to give me more business.

347
00:13:36,549 --> 00:13:39,185
THE LOVING BOYFRIEND'S SOLUTION

348
00:13:39,251 --> 00:13:41,053
-Chef Hyun-suk.
-Yes?

349
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,121
You want to do it, right?

350
00:13:42,188 --> 00:13:44,089
The wedding song.

351
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:46,725
-Do you want me to give you what you want?
-No, what about Eun-yeong?

352
00:13:46,792 --> 00:13:48,828
Do you need a singer, Eun-yeong?

353
00:13:50,396 --> 00:13:52,431
WE GOT A GOOD CLIP TO AIR

354
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:53,933
-Here's the thing.
-Yes?

355
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,602
She already talked to me last week.

356
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:59,672
She said, "Chef Hyun-suk,
will you sing at my wedding?"

357
00:13:59,738 --> 00:14:00,806
So I made myself clear.

358
00:14:00,873 --> 00:14:03,375
"You know many celebrities
and singers that can sing."

359
00:14:03,442 --> 00:14:05,911
"Why are you asking me?"

360
00:14:05,978 --> 00:14:08,848
I turned her down,
but she still wanted me to do it.

361
00:14:08,914 --> 00:14:10,115
-Wait, look.
-Really?

362
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:13,419
Chef Eun-yeong, you can relax
and tell us what happened.

363
00:14:13,485 --> 00:14:15,621
I needed a wedding singer,

364
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:18,023
and he wanted to sing, so…

365
00:14:19,892 --> 00:14:20,726
HE MADE HIS CASE FIRST

366
00:14:20,793 --> 00:14:22,461
-She's so considerate.
-See?

367
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:23,762
Chef Nam-no.

368
00:14:23,829 --> 00:14:26,298
My dream

369
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:28,200
is to sing a wedding song
at a fish restaurant.

370
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:29,902
RESERVING HIS NEXT SINGING GIG

371
00:14:29,969 --> 00:14:32,037
You're doing well. So very well.

372
00:14:32,104 --> 00:14:33,906
-Happy now?
-Good one, Hyun-suk.

373
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:35,341
Are you happy now?

374
00:14:35,407 --> 00:14:36,909
It's an emergency for Eun-yeong's wedding.

375
00:14:36,976 --> 00:14:40,746
We're all glad to hear
a lot of happy news.

376
00:14:40,813 --> 00:14:44,783
We're about to take a look
at Tiffany's fridge.

377
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:46,518
It's special, isn't it?

378
00:14:46,585 --> 00:14:48,254
Do you smell that?

379
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:51,891
-Something smells sweet.
-Yes, indeed.

380
00:14:51,957 --> 00:14:53,759
Does he also use this fridge?

381
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:56,128
-Probably.
-Probably.

382
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:58,030
HOW CUTE

383
00:14:58,097 --> 00:14:59,465
Is this the first time you're seeing it?

384
00:14:59,531 --> 00:15:01,400
Yes, I'm dying to see it too.

385
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:04,236
I want to see
what on earth she eats at home.

386
00:15:04,303 --> 00:15:06,105
-It's a married friend's fridge.
-It is.

387
00:15:06,171 --> 00:15:07,873
We'll see once we open it.

388
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:10,209
What kind of ingredients
does she keep inside?

389
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:12,745
-We present Tiffany's fridge!
-Fridge!

390
00:15:12,811 --> 00:15:14,146
-Fridge!
-Fridge!

391
00:15:14,213 --> 00:15:17,082
-You have lots of stuff inside.
-It's really neat.

392
00:15:17,149 --> 00:15:19,385
PRESENTING TIFFANY'S FRIDGE

393
00:15:19,451 --> 00:15:21,921
-It's really neat.
-She has lots of stuff.

394
00:15:21,987 --> 00:15:23,689
-I knew it. It shows her personality.
-I get it.

395
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:26,125
THE QUEEN OF NEATNESS

396
00:15:26,191 --> 00:15:29,194
I see yogurt on the top shelf.

397
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:31,730
Greek yogurt and some protein drinks.

398
00:15:31,797 --> 00:15:33,599
I keep my breakfast simple,

399
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:37,870
such as yogurt and fruit.

400
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:39,939
What about lunch and dinner?

401
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:42,141
I usually eat a salad for lunch

402
00:15:42,207 --> 00:15:45,277
and Korean cuisine for dinner.

403
00:15:45,344 --> 00:15:47,179
And among Korean cuisine,

404
00:15:47,246 --> 00:15:49,548
-I really love bibimbap.
-Bibimbap.

405
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:51,817
It's like salad with rice, right?

406
00:15:51,884 --> 00:15:54,286
I like salads and seasoned vegetables.

407
00:15:54,353 --> 00:15:56,622
Bibimbap, something with lots of veggies.

408
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:59,291
These are mostly used
to make Western food.

409
00:15:59,358 --> 00:16:00,559
Cheese and…

410
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:02,494
There's a type of cheese

411
00:16:02,561 --> 00:16:05,230
with lots of holes in them, Swiss cheese.

412
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:07,266
That's my favorite.

413
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:08,634
Do you also like Western cuisine?

414
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:11,737
I love Korean food,
but I also love Italian.

415
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,339
SHE PREFERS ITALIAN DISHES

416
00:16:13,405 --> 00:16:15,607
I especially love a dish
called <i>cacio e pepe.</i>

417
00:16:15,674 --> 00:16:16,976
<i>Cacio e pepe.</i>

418
00:16:17,042 --> 00:16:18,677
<i>Cacio </i>means "cheese,"

419
00:16:18,744 --> 00:16:21,613
and <i>e pepe</i> means "and black pepper."

420
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:25,884
It's simple yet difficult to make.

421
00:16:25,951 --> 00:16:27,586
Peanut butter.

422
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,088
I've never seen the orange lid one.

423
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:30,155
You're right.

424
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:34,760
-Honey roasted?
-When I lived with my members in Korea,

425
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:37,429
we always ate peanut butter with apples.

426
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:38,397
CLAP!

427
00:16:38,464 --> 00:16:41,800
Yes, that was a thing for a while.
Olive oil, apple, and peanut butter.

428
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:44,303
-It's the fad these days too.
-We did it back then.

429
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:46,605
We started back in middle school,
thanks to her.

430
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:48,073
-Middle school?
-Even back then,

431
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:51,410
-she'd slap it on apples to eat it.
-I ate it like that.

432
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:53,379
That means she started the fad.

433
00:16:53,445 --> 00:16:54,813
-Gosh.
-The originator.

434
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:55,981
It's not widely known,

435
00:16:56,048 --> 00:16:59,084
but people in the States
love to eat celery with peanut butter.

436
00:16:59,151 --> 00:17:01,854
So these days,
I suggest that people try it like that.

437
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,288
-I see.
-I'll try that.

438
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:05,891
Does he also enjoy
peanut butter and apples?

439
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:09,161
-Of course.
-I see.

440
00:17:09,228 --> 00:17:12,965
Among Girls' Generation,
Tiffany is known as the gourmet.

441
00:17:13,031 --> 00:17:14,299
She is.

442
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:18,537
I believe she was the one
who opened the door to fine dining.

443
00:17:18,604 --> 00:17:19,738
-Is that right?
-Really?

444
00:17:19,805 --> 00:17:22,574
I always loved fine dining and went often.

445
00:17:22,775 --> 00:17:23,776
YOU DID

446
00:17:23,842 --> 00:17:27,579
When we're on a tour,
we usually have to eat as a group,

447
00:17:27,646 --> 00:17:32,217
and my members say everything I pick
is delicious and go with it.

448
00:17:32,284 --> 00:17:34,319
-So I usually picked the menu.
-I see.

449
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:36,922
That sounds like her specialty.

450
00:17:36,989 --> 00:17:39,291
There's a reason why you let her do it.

451
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:41,060
-Yes.
-Right.

452
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:43,062
WHAT WAS THAT PAUSE?

453
00:17:43,128 --> 00:17:45,597
Did you find out
about fine dining because of her?

454
00:17:45,664 --> 00:17:47,299
Whenever we had to celebrate,

455
00:17:47,366 --> 00:17:49,301
we often went to an Italian restaurant.

456
00:17:49,368 --> 00:17:50,202
We did.

457
00:17:50,269 --> 00:17:53,539
But I guess she didn't notice
that I had a poor appetite on those days.

458
00:17:54,373 --> 00:17:57,242
THE TRUTH FINALLY COMES OUT?!

459
00:17:57,309 --> 00:18:00,546
Were there hits and misses
among the dishes

460
00:18:00,612 --> 00:18:02,848
-that she picked out?
-Most were good.

461
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,983
But I'm the type

462
00:18:05,050 --> 00:18:07,086
who loves local food

463
00:18:07,152 --> 00:18:09,288
made with strong spices.

464
00:18:09,354 --> 00:18:10,622
So I often couldn't finish the food,

465
00:18:10,689 --> 00:18:13,158
and even thought,
"I want to go home and eat <i>ramyeon</i>."

466
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:14,426
RAMYEON AFTER DINNER

467
00:18:14,493 --> 00:18:15,327
I understand.

468
00:18:15,394 --> 00:18:16,795
I see.

469
00:18:16,862 --> 00:18:18,430
Is there anything you don't eat?

470
00:18:18,997 --> 00:18:20,632
Liver, <i>sundae…</i>

471
00:18:20,699 --> 00:18:22,301
Whatever that is inside.

472
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:24,570
WHATEVER THAT'S INSIDE IS OUT

473
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:27,039
Another dish that I still find
difficult to handle is…

474
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:28,207
-Tripe?
-It's…

475
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:29,274
feet.

476
00:18:29,341 --> 00:18:32,344
-Chicken feet or pig's feet.
-Chicken feet, pig's feet.

477
00:18:32,411 --> 00:18:35,747
But she's a huge fan of chicken feet.

478
00:18:35,814 --> 00:18:37,015
-Do you love chicken feet?
-Yes.

479
00:18:37,082 --> 00:18:39,818
I like all kinds of feet.

480
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,020
THESE FEET ARE A BIT TOO SALTY

481
00:18:42,087 --> 00:18:44,156
-They're so different.
-Then you wouldn't eat

482
00:18:44,223 --> 00:18:45,457
<i>beondegi</i>, silkworm pupae.

483
00:18:45,524 --> 00:18:47,526
-No.
-It's a lump of protein.

484
00:18:47,593 --> 00:18:48,694
You know,

485
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:52,898
we lived together for 13 years, right?

486
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,299
One day, at our dorm,

487
00:18:54,366 --> 00:18:58,036
I saw her doing something
in the kitchen by the stove.

488
00:18:58,303 --> 00:18:59,771
WHAT WAS SHE DOING?

489
00:18:59,838 --> 00:19:00,839
I said…

490
00:19:01,373 --> 00:19:02,608
It smelled so…

491
00:19:02,674 --> 00:19:03,842
"What's this smell?"

492
00:19:03,909 --> 00:19:05,444
-It was so shocking.
-It smells good.

493
00:19:05,511 --> 00:19:06,712
WHAT WAS IT?

494
00:19:06,778 --> 00:19:11,016
And she was cooking something
in that yellow, vintage pot.

495
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,852
YELLOW, VINTAGE?

496
00:19:13,919 --> 00:19:16,788
-A nickel-silver pot.
-A nickel-silver pot.

497
00:19:16,855 --> 00:19:19,558
-Really?
-That's what "yellow and vintage" is?

498
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:21,760
The yellow, vintage pot
was a nickel-silver pot.

499
00:19:24,096 --> 00:19:26,365
-It sounds so classy.
-Yellow, vintage pot.

500
00:19:26,431 --> 00:19:29,434
So that was really shocking for me.

501
00:19:29,501 --> 00:19:33,005
Even then, she said,
"Do you know how much protein this has?"

502
00:19:33,071 --> 00:19:34,907
-And she enjoyed it a lot.
-It does.

503
00:19:34,973 --> 00:19:37,376
When I was younger, my mom often made

504
00:19:37,442 --> 00:19:40,112
<i>beondegi-tang</i>, silkworm pupae soup,
in an earthen pot.

505
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,347
-With garlic and pepper powder.
-With spicy pepper.

506
00:19:42,414 --> 00:19:44,116
You have to use Cheongyang pepper.

507
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:46,185
-Yes, with Cheongyang pepper.
-That's a lot of love.

508
00:19:46,251 --> 00:19:47,886
It's like that fable,
"The Fox and the Stork."

509
00:19:48,253 --> 00:19:51,456
THEIR TASTE IN FOOD
IS IN TWO DIFFERENT WORLDS

510
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,692
-The third shelf.
-Korean food.

511
00:19:53,759 --> 00:19:56,228
Korean food, some side dishes.
This looks like fresh kimchi.

512
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:58,163
Is this <i>gejang</i> in soy sauce?

513
00:19:58,230 --> 00:19:59,398
Seasoned spinach.

514
00:19:59,464 --> 00:20:00,799
-Squid.
-Seasoned squid strips.

515
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,067
-What's this?
-Rolled omelet.

516
00:20:02,134 --> 00:20:03,535
-Anchovies.
-Anchovies.

517
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:05,337
-Bellflower root.
-Bellflower root.

518
00:20:05,404 --> 00:20:07,139
-Seasoned vegetables.
-Those look awesome.

519
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,540
They're all my favorites.

520
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:09,775
You have lots of side dishes.

521
00:20:09,841 --> 00:20:11,610
Hey, you're a good cook.

522
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:13,712
-No way. Did you do it?
-Did you make this?

523
00:20:13,779 --> 00:20:15,681
No, it wasn't me.

524
00:20:15,747 --> 00:20:19,551
-It was my mother-in-law.
-Yo-han's mother.

525
00:20:19,618 --> 00:20:21,086
She's such a great cook.

526
00:20:21,153 --> 00:20:24,957
She always makes a huge feast for me
whenever we go over to eat.

527
00:20:25,023 --> 00:20:28,961
Is there anything that you made?
Something we can try?

528
00:20:31,296 --> 00:20:33,165
BUT

529
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:36,969
But I have a partner now,
so I have more interest

530
00:20:37,035 --> 00:20:39,538
in doing something like that.

531
00:20:39,605 --> 00:20:41,840
-You two are both busy.
-Yes, so not yet.

532
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:45,677
-But she'll teach me how to make kimchi.
-Making kimchi?

533
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:47,279
-I'm jealous.
-Little by little.

534
00:20:47,346 --> 00:20:48,780
-What's this?
-Sea urchin roe.

535
00:20:48,847 --> 00:20:51,283
Sea urchin roe? You have a lot.

536
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,684
How do you eat this?

537
00:20:52,751 --> 00:20:54,219
It's good no matter how you eat it.

538
00:20:54,286 --> 00:20:57,889
-You can eat it as is.
-Yes, you don't have to do anything.

539
00:20:57,956 --> 00:20:59,891
Do you prefer seafood to meat?

540
00:21:00,459 --> 00:21:01,760
-Yes.
-Seafood over meat.

541
00:21:01,827 --> 00:21:02,961
-I think so.
-Seafood.

542
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:05,097
How many tubes
of condensed milk do you have?

543
00:21:05,163 --> 00:21:06,999
Two, four, six, eight, nine. Nine?

544
00:21:07,065 --> 00:21:08,267
-Nine?
-Condensed milk?

545
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:09,768
Do you have a sweet tooth?

546
00:21:09,835 --> 00:21:11,069
I really do.

547
00:21:11,136 --> 00:21:13,438
-I love desserts so much.
-Me too!

548
00:21:15,073 --> 00:21:16,408
THAT WAS SUDDEN!

549
00:21:16,475 --> 00:21:17,709
It was like a love confession.

550
00:21:17,776 --> 00:21:20,145
-But you like everything.
-It's condensed milk.

551
00:21:20,212 --> 00:21:23,315
-It tastes good out of the tube.
-I just… Right?

552
00:21:23,382 --> 00:21:25,617
-With what? Just that?
-That was why…

553
00:21:25,684 --> 00:21:27,052
-Just squeeze it out.
-…back when we toured,

554
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:28,353
-we always had…
-Strawberries.

555
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:32,658
…a fridge full of condensed milk
and strawberries.

556
00:21:32,724 --> 00:21:34,192
Are strawberries your favorite fruit?

557
00:21:34,259 --> 00:21:37,429
I also love figs and persimmons.

558
00:21:37,496 --> 00:21:38,664
-Persimmons.
-Persimmons.

559
00:21:38,730 --> 00:21:40,165
-So you like all fruits?
-Yes.

560
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:41,333
She likes fruit.

561
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,768
-Vegetables.
-Now, vegetables.

562
00:21:42,834 --> 00:21:45,103
-Romaine?
-Romaine? Yes, romaine lettuce.

563
00:21:45,170 --> 00:21:46,872
Celery. Celery sticks.

564
00:21:46,938 --> 00:21:48,473
Apple mint.

565
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:49,708
Cabbage.

566
00:21:49,775 --> 00:21:52,878
This must be Yo-han's food.
Chicken breast.

567
00:21:52,944 --> 00:21:54,212
IS THE CHICKEN HER HUSBAND'S?

568
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:56,048
-It's not his.
-It's not.

569
00:21:56,114 --> 00:21:56,982
Is it yours?

570
00:21:57,049 --> 00:21:58,684
It's for my dogs.

571
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:00,485
INGREDIENT FOR HER DOGS

572
00:22:00,552 --> 00:22:02,921
-We have three dogs at home.
-Three?

573
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:07,326
Yes, my dogs are named
Prince and Princess,

574
00:22:07,392 --> 00:22:11,229
and Yo-han's dog is named Bokja,
a very cute…

575
00:22:11,296 --> 00:22:13,965
-Wait.
-Prince, Princess, and Bokja.

576
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,835
Hey, Okja.

577
00:22:16,902 --> 00:22:18,704
-Why is one suddenly Bokja?
-Okja out of the blue.

578
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:21,773
So for our dogs,
we either cook the meat ourselves

579
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:25,377
or try to find something organic

580
00:22:25,444 --> 00:22:26,778
-for their meals.
-Right.

581
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:30,849
At least to our dogs,
I believe I'm the best cook.

582
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:33,151
And down here, I found some seafood.

583
00:22:33,218 --> 00:22:35,821
-Scallops. Squid.
-You can never fail

584
00:22:35,887 --> 00:22:38,957
-with those ingredients.
-And meat. A pack of meat.

585
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:42,027
-She really loves sweets. Ice cream.
-Ice cream.

586
00:22:42,094 --> 00:22:45,797
I can never quit eating ice cream.

587
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:49,468
-You have this one.
-It's <i>riso</i>, rice gelato, which I love.

588
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:52,270
-Italian gelato.
-I can finish that tub in one sitting.

589
00:22:52,337 --> 00:22:55,407
-Are these mint chocolate chip?
-Mint chocolate chip.

590
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:57,376
WINCES AT MINT CHOCOLATE CHIP

591
00:22:57,442 --> 00:22:59,044
This is either a hit or a miss.

592
00:22:59,111 --> 00:23:00,379
You don't like it?

593
00:23:01,246 --> 00:23:03,081
It's a bull's eye for me.

594
00:23:03,148 --> 00:23:05,517
All our members love mint chocolate chip.

595
00:23:05,584 --> 00:23:07,352
No!

596
00:23:07,919 --> 00:23:10,288
Let's do a show of hands.
Who likes mint chocolate chip?

597
00:23:10,355 --> 00:23:12,824
LOVES MINT CHOCOLATE CHIP:
SON JONG-WON & SAM KIM

598
00:23:13,191 --> 00:23:15,560
EDDIE IS IN THE MIDDLE

599
00:23:16,194 --> 00:23:17,729
NOT AS MANY AS SHE THOUGHT

600
00:23:17,796 --> 00:23:19,831
I guess there are more haters.
Who hates it?

601
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:21,366
I really don't like it.

602
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:23,168
MOST OF THEM DO NOT LIKE IT

603
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:24,503
I even hate it

604
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:26,738
when the mint ice cream
touches another flavor.

605
00:23:27,038 --> 00:23:28,340
YOU HATE IT THAT MUCH?

606
00:23:28,407 --> 00:23:29,875
It's like a trap.

607
00:23:29,941 --> 00:23:31,777
We'd buy a gallon of ice cream

608
00:23:31,843 --> 00:23:33,378
full of only mint chocolate chip flavor.

609
00:23:33,445 --> 00:23:37,182
So during a shoot, we only had
mint chocolate chip ice cream and spoons.

610
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:39,017
People who don't like it say

611
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:41,019
it's because it tastes like toothpaste,

612
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:43,121
so why do the lovers love it?

613
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:44,222
-Jong-won.
-Yes, why?

614
00:23:44,289 --> 00:23:45,223
Do you like toothpaste?

615
00:23:45,290 --> 00:23:48,059
-Why do you like it, Jong-won?
-He must like to brush his teeth.

616
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:49,728
I don't understand why it's debated.

617
00:23:49,795 --> 00:23:52,130
-Why not?
-When we mention ice cream flavors,

618
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:55,534
most people love
vanilla, chocolate, and strawberry, right?

619
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,670
I think mint chocolate chip
should be on par with those.

620
00:23:58,737 --> 00:23:59,938
It's a classic flavor.

621
00:24:00,005 --> 00:24:02,874
No one hates chocolate, right?
So that's how it feels.

622
00:24:02,941 --> 00:24:05,310
-Of course, it's good.
-Who made mint chocolate chip anyway?

623
00:24:05,377 --> 00:24:07,712
All of Girls' Generation love
mint chocolate chip,

624
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:09,748
but you don't, Sung-jun?

625
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:12,584
I don't think I can copy that.

626
00:24:12,651 --> 00:24:14,619
-You can't do it.
-I understand. I respect that.

627
00:24:16,321 --> 00:24:18,457
-There's a bakery here.
-It's a bakery.

628
00:24:18,523 --> 00:24:21,626
My favorites are sourdough and focaccia.

629
00:24:21,693 --> 00:24:23,662
It's great in San Francisco.

630
00:24:23,728 --> 00:24:26,198
Who eats this soup made with Korean beef?

631
00:24:26,264 --> 00:24:28,200
That'll be me.

632
00:24:28,266 --> 00:24:29,601
-Do you eat this?
-You like <i>dogani-tang?</i>

633
00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:32,370
I once hurt my ligament while performing,

634
00:24:32,437 --> 00:24:33,505
and I tried it then.

635
00:24:33,572 --> 00:24:34,573
To help your bones mend?

636
00:24:34,639 --> 00:24:36,908
-It felt like it worked!
-Did it really?

637
00:24:36,975 --> 00:24:38,777
FELT LIKE OX KNEE SOUP WAS EFFECTIVE

638
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:41,279
So I became rather interested
in healthy food.

639
00:24:41,346 --> 00:24:42,747
Tiffany is a gourmet,

640
00:24:42,814 --> 00:24:45,650
so let's find out
what orders she'll make today.

641
00:24:45,717 --> 00:24:48,286
Let's find out her orders. Show us!

642
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:52,657
Fine… No. Fany Dining, Love It.

643
00:24:52,724 --> 00:24:54,926
Fine dining? No.

644
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:58,063
-Fany Dining.
-Fany Dining.

645
00:24:58,129 --> 00:25:00,999
I really love the fine dining experience,

646
00:25:01,066 --> 00:25:04,669
and where else will I get to enjoy
something like this?

647
00:25:04,736 --> 00:25:08,773
So I want to have
the fine dining experience made for me.

648
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,308
Let's move on to the next order.

649
00:25:10,375 --> 00:25:11,209
The second order.

650
00:25:12,811 --> 00:25:15,480
We Can't Stop! It's Fany Time.

651
00:25:15,547 --> 00:25:17,482
There's a lot to celebrate lately,

652
00:25:17,549 --> 00:25:21,353
so I wanted to have a festive time
and throw a party for myself.

653
00:25:21,419 --> 00:25:23,088
I'm interested in that.

654
00:25:23,154 --> 00:25:24,523
A DISH TO HELP HER CELEBRATE

655
00:25:24,589 --> 00:25:27,192
We have nine chefs in the studio today,

656
00:25:27,259 --> 00:25:29,327
-so one of you can sit out.
-One.

657
00:25:29,394 --> 00:25:32,697
I've already cooked for them once before.

658
00:25:32,764 --> 00:25:34,966
-They came to your restaurant.
-Yes.

659
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:38,837
So I thought they should try
other chefs' dishes this time.

660
00:25:38,904 --> 00:25:41,072
So I'd like to step back.

661
00:25:41,139 --> 00:25:42,774
Let's decide on the contenders.

662
00:25:42,841 --> 00:25:44,976
Chef Eddie hasn't been here for a while,

663
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:47,913
-so you can go first.
-Really? Thank you.

664
00:25:47,979 --> 00:25:50,982
I really love parties,

665
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:53,952
so I'll choose
We Can't Stop! It's Fany Time.

666
00:25:54,019 --> 00:25:55,186
-Party food.
-Yes.

667
00:25:55,253 --> 00:25:57,322
-Do you like parties?
-Of course.

668
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:58,590
It sounds great.

669
00:25:58,657 --> 00:26:01,393
-His hair is festive.
-Yes, his hair is festive.

670
00:26:03,528 --> 00:26:07,299
I also specialize in banquets and feasts.

671
00:26:07,365 --> 00:26:09,067
-Banquets and feasts.
-Feasts.

672
00:26:09,134 --> 00:26:13,238
I'd like to fight Chef Edward.
We Can't Stop! It's Fany Time.

673
00:26:13,305 --> 00:26:15,640
A dish suitable for a party.

674
00:26:15,707 --> 00:26:19,477
Chef Eun-yeong, who's also about to marry,
takes the party food.

675
00:26:19,544 --> 00:26:21,313
One round has been decided.

676
00:26:21,379 --> 00:26:23,782
-Next, Fany Dining.
-Fine dining.

677
00:26:24,049 --> 00:26:25,817
RAISING HAND

678
00:26:25,884 --> 00:26:28,353
Jong-won. Jong-won is in.

679
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:30,922
SAM KIM RAISES HIS HAND TOO

680
00:26:30,989 --> 00:26:32,557
Oh, yeah.

681
00:26:32,624 --> 00:26:36,895
Jong-won and Sam join
the fine dining round.

682
00:26:36,962 --> 00:26:39,030
-They have the most stars, right?
-They have

683
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:41,132
-the most stars at the moment.
-They do.

684
00:26:41,199 --> 00:26:42,701
-Four and four.
-One will get five.

685
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:45,770
-You two have one each?
-Yes.

686
00:26:46,471 --> 00:26:47,806
I GOT 3

687
00:26:47,872 --> 00:26:48,707
You have three?

688
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:50,375
Thanks to Chinese food.

689
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:51,509
YOUNG GUNS, ALWAYS FRIENDLY

690
00:26:51,576 --> 00:26:54,946
The first round is Fany Dining,

691
00:26:55,013 --> 00:26:58,450
Chef Jong-won versus Chef Sam!

692
00:27:01,386 --> 00:27:05,757
<i>We're about to begin the first round</i>
<i>with ingredients from Tiffany's fridge.</i>

693
00:27:05,824 --> 00:27:08,760
The superstar of children,
Chef Son Jong-won,

694
00:27:08,827 --> 00:27:13,765
versus children's favorite gentleman,
Chef Sam Kim.

695
00:27:13,832 --> 00:27:15,867
They both have four stars,

696
00:27:15,934 --> 00:27:18,370
so they currently share the lead.

697
00:27:18,436 --> 00:27:20,372
The winner of this round

698
00:27:20,438 --> 00:27:23,108
will become the sole first place.

699
00:27:23,174 --> 00:27:25,143
It's a big match.

700
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:27,746
We have the same number of stars,

701
00:27:27,812 --> 00:27:32,751
so I always thought we'd face a day
when we decide who'll take the lead.

702
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:34,352
So you don't want to share the lead?

703
00:27:34,419 --> 00:27:36,521
I don't find it uncomfortable,

704
00:27:36,588 --> 00:27:39,224
-but we should decide on the ranking.
-We must decide!

705
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:40,358
-I see.
-He's a fighter.

706
00:27:40,425 --> 00:27:41,559
First place is for one person.

707
00:27:41,626 --> 00:27:42,927
Let's see who's on the top.

708
00:27:42,994 --> 00:27:45,563
Poong will fall off eventually, anyway.

709
00:27:45,630 --> 00:27:47,799
So all he has to do now
is beat Jong-won to lead.

710
00:27:47,866 --> 00:27:49,334
That's true.

711
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:52,070
Chef Jong-won,
are you also conscious of Chef Sam?

712
00:27:52,137 --> 00:27:54,239
Of course. Very much so.

713
00:27:54,305 --> 00:27:55,774
-So honest.
-They must bother each other.

714
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:59,511
One of the biggest joys
in my everyday life

715
00:27:59,577 --> 00:28:02,814
<i>has been reading the letters</i>
<i>sent to me from elementary school kids.</i>

716
00:28:02,881 --> 00:28:04,916
It's so comforting to read their letters,

717
00:28:04,983 --> 00:28:08,987
but I recently heard
that many of them crossed over to Sam.

718
00:28:09,054 --> 00:28:11,489
I haven't been getting
as many letters lately.

719
00:28:11,556 --> 00:28:12,857
I've had

720
00:28:12,924 --> 00:28:14,793
many more letters recently.

721
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:16,528
-You have?
-Just a tad bit.

722
00:28:16,594 --> 00:28:18,096
As your performance improved.

723
00:28:18,163 --> 00:28:20,799
Sam is on a roll these days
with a streak of four wins.

724
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:23,668
-Really?
-You won four rounds in a row.

725
00:28:23,735 --> 00:28:27,605
And today, you're facing Chef Jong-won.

726
00:28:27,672 --> 00:28:29,841
Jong-won says
he's confident about this order.

727
00:28:29,908 --> 00:28:31,176
HE FEELS CONFIDENT?

728
00:28:31,242 --> 00:28:32,944
Were you born in San Francisco?

729
00:28:33,011 --> 00:28:34,145
Yes.

730
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:35,814
WHAT DOES THAT HAVE TO DO WITH HIM?

731
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:38,083
Following Seoul, the place
where I have lived the longest at

732
00:28:38,149 --> 00:28:39,884
was San Francisco.

733
00:28:39,951 --> 00:28:40,919
For how many years?

734
00:28:40,985 --> 00:28:42,587
Six to seven years.

735
