979
00:37:55,606 --> 00:37:56,641
You needed more water?

980
00:37:56,707 --> 00:37:59,210
-That was a surprise.
-What's up?

981
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:00,911
POURING 2 L WITH ONE HAND

982
00:38:00,978 --> 00:38:02,813
He poured the whole thing in.

983
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:05,216
He used to be more calm.

984
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:06,884
It's an emergency.

985
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:09,186
SOMETHING HAS AWOKEN IN HIM

986
00:38:09,253 --> 00:38:11,122
-Seven minutes.
-You have to steam them.

987
00:38:11,188 --> 00:38:12,790
Time really flies.

988
00:38:14,225 --> 00:38:15,726
-Three minutes each…
-Six minutes and fifty seconds.

989
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:18,195
My heart is racing as I watch.

990
00:38:18,262 --> 00:38:19,764
Why didn't you use the water
in the kettle?

991
00:38:19,830 --> 00:38:21,299
-Yes, that's cold water.
-It's cold.

992
00:38:21,365 --> 00:38:23,434
It's boiling right now.

993
00:38:23,501 --> 00:38:25,603
It's an emergency.

994
00:38:25,670 --> 00:38:26,504
He'll steam those?

995
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:27,405
SETS THE TIMER

996
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:28,839
He begins to steam it.

997
00:38:28,906 --> 00:38:30,875
It looks like he's short on time.

998
00:38:30,941 --> 00:38:32,243
You have to make four dishes.

999
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:33,911
They haven't even finished one.

1000
00:38:33,978 --> 00:38:37,715
2. TOAST BREAD WITHOUT CRUST
