1045
00:40:13,711 --> 00:40:15,446
LOOKS LIKE AMY'S PASTA

1046
00:40:15,513 --> 00:40:17,415
That happens when I make it at home.

1047
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:18,983
-Amy's pasta.
-Yes, Amy's pasta.

1048
00:40:19,049 --> 00:40:21,986
I also made that face
when my scorched rice got ruined.

1049
00:40:22,052 --> 00:40:23,621
It's an emergency.

1050
00:40:23,687 --> 00:40:25,990
-This is definitely burnt.
-It is.

1051
00:40:26,056 --> 00:40:27,391
-Sung-ju.
-Look at that.

1052
00:40:27,458 --> 00:40:29,593
-Can you try it?
-That's Amy's pasta.

1053
00:40:29,660 --> 00:40:31,529
-Does it taste burnt?
-It'll be too hard.

1054
00:40:31,595 --> 00:40:32,930
It's way too hard.

1055
00:40:32,997 --> 00:40:33,998
-No.
-How's the texture?

1056
00:40:34,064 --> 00:40:37,334
Is it truly Sam's generation right now?

1057
00:40:38,235 --> 00:40:39,503
I think it's over!

1058
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:41,505
What do you mean?

1059
00:40:41,572 --> 00:40:44,041
-It turns hard when it's burnt.
-It's not cooked yet.

1060
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:45,176
It turns hard when burnt.

1061
00:40:45,242 --> 00:40:47,711
You have to pull the noodles out early
to make <i>cacio e pepe.</i>

1062
00:40:47,778 --> 00:40:50,681
-That way, it gives out more starch.
-Really?

1063
00:40:50,748 --> 00:40:53,651
-You have to get it out early for starch.
-Really?

1064
00:40:53,717 --> 00:40:56,454
-Otherwise, the sauce won't get thick.
-Is that so?

1065
00:40:56,720 --> 00:40:57,855
JONG-WON MOVES ON!

